snippet.textDisplay: If you guys have the chance or are traveling to Houston any time soon, there is a funeral museum there with lots of cool exhibits about mummification, cremation, coffins, how popes are buried, military funerals, hearses, and the funerals of some American Presidents.  There is one particular casket that has a very interesting but also tragic backstory.  The casket is three times wider than a traditional casket because it was built to hold three people, two adults and a child.  The story goes, there was a young couple that lost their child.  Unable to cope, they made a murder-suicide pact so that they could be buried with their lost child.  They had the casket made, but they never went through with the plan.  They ended up divorced.  The casket maker was out the cost of the casket and he couldn't use it for anything else so he eventually donated it to the museum.
